  {
    "client_msg_id": "f5c4ddcc-4eca-47a9-b80c-b51300e3e7fa",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Or here's another abstraction leak: floating point arithmetic, and I don't mean `0.1 + 0.2 != 0.3`.  Today, as on most days, I was doing a linear optimization (find a solution) followed by a quadratic optimization (find the best solution).  The quadratic optimization conceptually has a feasible solution (you already have one in hand), but finding it is too much for solver.  So the fix is to cut the solver some slack, find the best solution within about 0.000000001% of the answer.",
    "user": "UA14TGLTC",
    "ts": "1539253010.000100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
