  {
    "client_msg_id": "64e3aab8-faac-45a9-a653-e79ae89ff938",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Also, add me to the anti-abstraction _copyista_ side: <https://lobste.rs/s/zyomiu/what_does_it_mean_design_software_well#c_yvvkwm>.\n\n<@U8A5MS6R1> in particular seeing abstraction as compression is misleading in the extreme, because lots of great compression schemes are terrible abstractions. Your compass does not point due North.\n\nIt's worth keeping the end in mind: holding complex programs in our heads. \"Abstraction\" is a siren, a tantalizing idea that causes us to forget the goal. Mistrust it. Humans have a poor track record at holding programs in our heads, so consider the possibility that our mental models for what helps and what hurts are not yet fully baked.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
