  {
    "client_msg_id": "2b07b055-ac18-4e47-b894-1d3fb2f03b6c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I once wrote a Chrome extension to modify the Reddit UI in a small way: it would highlight any comment that had a higher score than its parent comment. This is a great heuristic for finding excellent comments.\n\nIt took me like a day to build. After a few months it broke -- I assume Reddit must’ve updated their UI some small way which broke my comment parsing. I never took the time to fix it.\n\nI’m not sure what the moral of this story is.",
    "user": "UDCLT064X",
    "ts": "1539296943.000100",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
